user_prompt_template:
As of {as_of}, does {company} have an identifiable moat from at least one of Morningstar's five sources (network effect, intangible assets like patents/brand/licenses, cost advantage, switching costs, or efficient scale), and is it wide (durable >20yr on current trajectory), narrow (durable ~10yr), or effectively none? Score 4 (wide moat, clearly identifiable source), 2 (narrow moat, real but time-limited advantage), or 0 (no identifiable moat) - based only on what was true and knowable as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, do {company}'s executives and directors hold a meaningful equity stake (real skin in the game) with no pattern of unusual heavy selling, or does insider ownership/recent transaction activity suggest weak alignment with shareholders? Score 2 (meaningful ownership, aligned), 1 (unclear/mixed signal), or 0 (low ownership or concerning selling pattern) - based only on what was knowable as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

Insider ownership % (if known): {insider_ownership_pct}
Recent insider transactions (if known): {insider_transactions}

As of {as_of}, is most of {company}'s revenue recurring/contracted (subscription, multi-year contracts, high renewal rates) rather than one-time/transactional/cyclical? Score 3 (majority recurring, e.g. >60% subscription/contracted), 1 (mixed model), or 0 (mostly one-time/transactional) - based on the business model as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, does {company} have a diversified customer base, or is a large share of revenue dependent on a small number of large customers (a single customer >10% of revenue is a common risk flag)? Score 2 (diversified, no concerning concentration), 1 (unclear/moderate concentration), or 0 (high concentration, real dependency risk) - based only on what was knowable as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

Largest customer(s) as % of revenue (if known): {customer_concentration_pct}

As of {as_of}, is {company}'s addressable market both large relative to its current revenue (meaningful runway left) and still growing (not mature/saturated/shrinking)? Score 4 (large + growing TAM, real runway), 2 (large but mature, or growing but already well-penetrated), or 0 (small and/or shrinking market) - based only on what was knowable as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, could {company} plausibly raise prices meaningfully without losing significant volume or customers (real pricing power), or would a price increase likely drive customers to substitutes (commodity-like, no pricing power)? Score 3 (clear pricing power - brand, switching costs, or lack of substitutes), 1 (some pricing power but constrained by competition), or 0 (commodity-like, minimal pricing power) - based only on what was knowable as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

As of {as_of}, does {company}'s competitive position look like it's strengthening (gaining share, widening cost/technology lead, deepening switching costs), holding steady, or eroding (losing share, new entrants closing the gap, technology being disrupted)? Score 2 (widening/strengthening), 1 (stable), or 0 (eroding) - based only on what was knowable as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

Named competitors and recent competitive dynamics (if known): {competitive_context}

As of {as_of}, is {company} meaningfully exposed to interest-rate moves (via financing costs, real-estate-like duration, a high-multiple growth valuation, or debt-funded business model), or is it largely insensitive to rates (low debt, stable cash-generative business, reasonable valuation)? Score 2 (largely rate-insensitive - a plus for a low-frequency, long-hold account), 1 (moderate sensitivity), or 0 (highly rate-sensitive) - based on the business/balance sheet as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

Sector: {sector}. Debt level context (if known): {leverage_context}

As of {as_of}, given the prevailing economic conditions and where the business cycle appears to be (early/mid/late expansion, or contraction), is {company}'s sector positioned favorably (a cyclical tailwind, or a defensive sector holding up in a downturn) or unfavorably (a cyclical headwind for its stage of the cycle)? Score 2 (favorably positioned for the current cycle stage), 1 (neutral/unclear), or 0 (unfavorably positioned) - based only on economic conditions knowable as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

Sector: {sector}. Macro/economic context as of {as_of} (if known): {macro_context}

As of {as_of}, is {company}'s profitability meaningfully exposed to swings in commodity input costs (energy, metals, agricultural inputs) or foreign-exchange rates (large non-domestic revenue/cost base) that it doesn't control or fully hedge? Score 2 (minimal exposure - domestic, low commodity intensity), 1 (moderate exposure), or 0 (high, largely uncontrolled exposure) - based on the business model as of {as_of}.

Company situation:
{company_brief}

Sector: {sector}. Geographic revenue mix (if known): {geo_revenue_mix}
